Package: DownBallotR
Title: Local and State Election Data via R with Python-Backed Scrapers
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Graham", "Chickering", email = "grahamchickering@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Chris", "Warshaw", email = "chris.warshaw@georgetown.edu", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Provides an R interface for downloading and standardizing local and state election data.
    The package wraps state-specific Python web scrapers (e.g., Playwright/requests-based) via reticulate,
    and exposes consistent R functions for querying election availability and results.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
